news.title: Indore: Buyers demand possession of plots during public hearing
news.para: “We are preparing a seniority list of members and the election of the society would be held soon. There are some other issues we are working on,” cooperative department deputy registrar Madan Gajbhiye said.

news.title: Visakhapatnam development body's auction may set new standard in plot prices
news.para: The VMRDA’s land auctions generally draw a huge number of applications due to the litigation-free nature of its lands.

news.title: Gujarat: 43% increase in stamp duty collection, 25% in sale deeds
news.para: Stamp duty revenue for 2018-19, 2019-20 and 2020-21 was Rs 7,781 crore, Rs 7,701 crore and Rs 7,390 crore, respectively. Compared to 2020-21, stamp duty in 2021-22 increased by more than Rs 3,000 crore.

news.title: Property tax hike for five zones released in Chennai
news.para: An Adyar resident living in a house ranging between 1,201 sq ft and 1,800 sq ft and paying half yearly property tax of Rs 1461 will now have to pay a maximum of Rs 2,922.

news.title: About 200 real estate projects stuck due to delay in approvals: Credai Indore
news.para: The real estate market has seen a rapid recovery post Covid-19 restrictions led by a significant jump in demand for plots and ready-to-move in properties by home buyers but the delay in mandatory permissions has blocked funds and stalled sales of units, claimed developers.

news.title: Ramky Group failed to pay, lied about land in township plan: HMDA to Telangana HC
news.para: Nearly 14 years after initiating the Discovery City project in Srinagar village, the HMDA had issued a termination notice to Ramky in August last year for not fulfilling its obligations as per the joint agreement to develop the township.

news.title: Maharashtra revenue minister to meet IGR on 10,500 illegal registration
news.para: "I will discuss with the IGR regarding these documents and what needs to be done," he said. Thorat added that he would direct officials to check the mutation entries of the documents carried out by the revenue department representatives from the collectorate.

news.title: Greater Noida: Panchsheel Greens 2 gets second tranche of SWAMIH funds
news.para: Out of the total of Rs 249 crore approved for Panchsheel Greens 2, a housing project by Panchsheel Buildtech, the stress fund is being released in four installments. The first tranche of about Rs 34 crore was released in September last year.

news.title: Bail plea of Rudra group's promoter accused of duping homebuyers rejected
news.para: As per the investigating officer (IO), during protection from arrest, Khurana did not cooperate in the investigation, additional sessions judge Anil Kumar noted.

news.title: Builders' body demands cement regulatory authority
news.para: ​The BAI has also urged the government for a 'unified standard contract document' to be adopted by all work authorities throughout the country including local bodies, state governments and corporations to weed out the benchmark variations.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Planners suggest wider roads to support taller buildings
news.para: ​In effect, the Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation (AMC) has suggested doing away with 6m, 9m and 12m roads in future town planning schemes. This is the first time this issue was discussed at a town planning committee meeting.

news.title: Indore: About 20 hectare land pooled so far for development of Pithampur sector 7
news.para: The existing industrial belt Pithampur, state’s largest industrial area, is expanded to attract fresh investments and accommodate more industries in the industrial belt.

news.title: Alliance Group plans to launch Rs 8,600 crore projects in Bengaluru, Chennai & Hyderabad
news.para: The company reported sales of Rs 2,290 crore for 2021-22 and sales of 3,686 homes, largely driven by the residential segment. “2021-22 was a remarkable year in our journey. In spite of the Covid-19 pandemic, we were able to cross many major milestones in the industry,” said Manoj Namburu, chairman, Alliance Group and Urbanrise.

news.title: Mysuru development body to regularise structures that have come up on notified land
news.para: Hundreds of acres of land that were acquired by Mysuru Urban Development Authority (Muda) for layout development and later were entangled in legal battle have been posing challenges to the urban body as structures have come up illegally.

news.title: Gurugram: Give flats in six months or pay 12% interest, builder told
news.para: Launched in 2008, ILD Greens in Sector 37C was to be delivered by 2013. But tower 2, which has 260 units, is still incomplete despite the allottees having paid around 90% of the dues. ILD Greens has a total of six towers, five of which have been completed.
